        <h2>The Father of the World Wide Web</h2>
        <p>A graduate of Oxford University, England. With a background of system design in real-time communications and text processing software development, in 1989 he invented the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('World Wide Web', 'WD'); ?>, an internet based hypermedia initiative for global information sharing while working at <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('CERN', 'C'); ?>, the European Particle Physics Laboratory. He wrote the first Web client (browser-editor) and server in 1990.</p>
        <p>Before coming to CERN, Tim worked with Image Computer Systems, of Ferndown, Dorset, England and before that as a principal engineer with Plessey Telecommunications, in Poole, England.</p>
